<subSubSection id="85EF16C9FFA07C6FFFD3F422FEB920E6" pageId="1" pageNumber="104" type="description">
<paragraph id="CD4A4542FFA07C6FFFD3F422FCF426E6" blockId="1.[113,1089,619,1603]" box="[113,797,619,643]" pageId="1" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis id="FF819950FFA07C6FFFD3F422FEFE26E6" bold="true" box="[113,279,619,643]" pageId="1" pageNumber="104">Redescription.</emphasis>
Male. Body length 
<quantity id="0A0DE8A7FFA07C6FFE49F422FDC226E6" box="[491,555,619,643]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="104" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
, primary colour black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD4A4542FFA07C6FFF32F4C2FF152726" blockId="1.[113,1089,619,1603]" pageId="1" pageNumber="104">Head. Dark, orbits, parafacialia, frontal vitta and hind portion of head black, face, genae and narrow strip in front of frontal vittae yellow, three pairs of frontal setae, two pairs of orbital setae, scape, pedicel and entire antennae including bare arista black, aristomere 3 long, three times as long as basally wide, second aristomere only slightly prolonged. Palpi yellow with yellow hairs, vibrissal callus with one vibrissa, and genae in hind portion with yellow hairs.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD4A4542FFA07C6FFF32F502FE1F27A6" blockId="1.[113,1089,619,1603]" pageId="1" pageNumber="104">
Thorax. Acrostichal bristles sparse, three distinct katepisternal bristles, two scutellar bristles, other chaetotaxy standard, wings hyaline, all veins distinct, vein Cu 
<subScript id="51714707FFA07C6FFCD6F532FC9527EF" attach="left" box="[884,892,891,906]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="104">1</subScript>
+ 1A ends at wing margin. All legs yellow, meso- and metafemora slightly darkened dorsoapically, procoxae distinctly and conspicuously yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD4A4542FFA07C6FFF32F582FC652006" blockId="1.[113,1089,619,1603]" pageId="1" pageNumber="104">
Abdomen. Sternite 4 very short and wider than long, sternite 3 rectangular and proximally with an incision, lobes of sternite 5 long, straight, only apically slightly narrowed, basal inner portion of lobes distinctly enlarged and with short bristles at its medial edges (
<figureCitation id="55CE59C7FFA07C6FFC3EF242FC302046" box="[924,985,1035,1059]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[151,190,1530,1549]" captionTargetBox="[215,1063,221,1466]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[209,1068,218,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1-6. 1-3: Amaurosoma longicorne (von Roser, 1840); 4-6: A. bernasconii sp. nov., male, holotype. 1, 4 – abdominal sternites 4 and 5; 2, 5 – surstyli and cerci; 3, 6 – praegonite. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs. 1-2, 4-5); 0.1 mm (Figs. 3, 6)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468111/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="104">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Surstyli slightly arched, with short and fine bristles on inner side, cerci short (
<figureCitation id="55CE59C7FFA07C6FFC8DF262FC842026" box="[815,877,1067,1091]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[151,190,1530,1549]" captionTargetBox="[215,1063,221,1466]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[209,1068,218,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1-6. 1-3: Amaurosoma longicorne (von Roser, 1840); 4-6: A. bernasconii sp. nov., male, holotype. 1, 4 – abdominal sternites 4 and 5; 2, 5 – surstyli and cerci; 3, 6 – praegonite. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs. 1-2, 4-5); 0.1 mm (Figs. 3, 6)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468111/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="104">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), praegonite straight and narrow, slightly broadened apically with one subapical bristle (
<figureCitation id="55CE59C7FFA07C6FFC9FF202FC972006" box="[829,894,1099,1123]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[151,190,1530,1549]" captionTargetBox="[215,1063,221,1466]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[209,1068,218,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1-6. 1-3: Amaurosoma longicorne (von Roser, 1840); 4-6: A. bernasconii sp. nov., male, holotype. 1, 4 – abdominal sternites 4 and 5; 2, 5 – surstyli and cerci; 3, 6 – praegonite. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs. 1-2, 4-5); 0.1 mm (Figs. 3, 6)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4468111" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4468111/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="104">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD4A4542FFA07C6FFF32F222FEB920E6" blockId="1.[113,1089,619,1603]" box="[144,336,1131,1155]" pageId="1" pageNumber="104">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="85EF16C9FFA07C6FFFD3F2C2FE2E2166" pageId="1" pageNumber="104" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CD4A4542FFA07C6FFFD3F2C2FE2E2166" blockId="1.[113,1089,619,1603]" pageId="1" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis id="FF819950FFA07C6FFFD3F2C2FE8520C6" bold="true" box="[113,364,1163,1187]" pageId="1" pageNumber="104">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="0AF53EC1FFA07C6FFED0F2C5FD9020C6" authorityName="SIFNER" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="von Roser" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[370,633,1164,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Amaurosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicorne">
<emphasis id="FF819950FFA07C6FFED0F2C5FD9020C6" box="[370,633,1164,1187]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="104">Amaurosoma longicorne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the nearest species, 
<taxonomicName id="0AF53EC1FFA07C6FFC7BF2C5FEED20A6" authority="Becker, 1894" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Amaurosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inerme">
<emphasis id="FF819950FFA07C6FFC7BF2C5FBA820C6" box="[985,1089,1164,1187]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="104">A. inerme</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A96438B3FFA07C6FFFD3F2E2FEED20A6" author="BECKER T." box="[113,260,1195,1219]" pageId="1" pageNumber="104" pagination="77 - 196" refId="ref2840" refString="BECKER T. 1894: Dipterologische Studien. I. Scatomyzidae. Berliner Entomologische Zeitschrift 39: 77 - 196." type="journal article" year="1894">Becker, 1894</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by the following characters: aristomere distinctly long, praegonite apically broadened with one subapical bristle, abdominal sternite 4 very short, and abdominal sternite 3 long with a proximal incision.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
