<paragraph id="CD4A4542FFA27C6DFF32F4F2FE052756" blockId="3.[113,1089,699,819]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">
Only the male from Malšice (
<collectingCountry id="B5E205D2FFA27C6DFE69F4F2FD9126B6" box="[459,632,699,723]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
) corresponds to the Becker’s redescription and differs from all species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="0AF53EC1FFA27C6DFDB6F495FD482696" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1894" box="[532,673,732,755]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Amaurosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FF819950FFA27C6DFDB6F495FD482696" box="[532,673,732,755]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Amaurosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: first aristomere long, praegonite broadened apically, and the shape of abdominal sternites 3-5 including lobes. I regard this species as valid.
</paragraph>
